## Optional Secrets

Add only if enabled:

```env
REDIS_PASSWORD=
DASHBOARD_SIGNING_KEY=
AWS_S3_MEDIA_BUCKET=
WHATSAPP_ONBOARDING_S3_MEDIA_BUCKET=
WHATSAPP_ONBOARDING_ANALYTICS_BUCKET=
SYNTHETIC_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
OPENAI_API_KEY=
LLM_PROVIDER_API_KEY=
```

## Must Review In GitHub Variables

These were uploaded with placeholder values and must be replaced before AWS deployment:

```text
AWS_DEV_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN
AWS_STAGING_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN
AWS_PROD_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN
AWS_TERRAFORM_PLAN_ROLE_ARN
ECS_SUBNET_IDS
ECS_SECURITY_GROUP_IDS
WEBHOOK_VERIFY_URL
SYNTHETIC_WEBHOOK_URL
```

Also confirm these match your actual AWS resources:

```text
APP_URL
ECR_REPOSITORY
ECS_CLUSTER
ECS_WEB_SERVICE
ECS_WORKER_SERVICE
ECS_WEB_TASK_FAMILY
ECS_WORKER_TASK_FAMILY
```

## Production Safety

Keep this value false until a test signup has been verified end to end:

```text
WHATSAPP_CREATE_REAL_PROFILE=false
```

After staging/test signup writes correctly to the existing `register` table, change production to:

```text
WHATSAPP_CREATE_REAL_PROFILE=true
```

## Media Storage Choice

If ECS can write to the same website storage path:

```text
MEDIA_STORAGE_DRIVER=legacy_public_user
WHATSAPP_ONBOARDING_LOCAL_MEDIA_PATH=storage/user
WHATSAPP_ONBOARDING_MEDIA_DB_VALUE=filename_only
```

If ECS is separate and cannot share `public/storage/user`, change to S3:

```text
MEDIA_STORAGE_DRIVER=s3
AWS_S3_MEDIA_PREFIX=nxtutors/onboarding
```

Then add the S3 bucket secrets listed above.

## Do Not Add

Do not add long-lived AWS access keys to GitHub:

```text
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
```

Use GitHub OIDC with AWS role ARN variables instead.

Do not create Lambda for the main agent:

```text
CREATE_LAMBDA_FUNCTION=false
DEPLOY_TARGET=ecs
```
